                 Two-Stage Fitting (TSFIT)
Version 1.00

This package contains a C/C++ software library implementing the two-stage scattered
data fitting method described in the following papers:

 O. Davydov and F. Zeilfelder, Scattered data fitting by direct extension 
 of local polynomials to bivariate splines, Advances in Comp. Math. 21 (2004), 223-271.

 O. Davydov, R. Morandi and A. Sestini, Local hybrid approximation for 
 scattered data fitting with bivariate splines, Comput. Aided Geom. Design 23 (2006), 703-721. 
 Preprint version is available from http://www.staff.uni-giessen.de/odavydov/hybrid.html
 
 O. Davydov, A. Sestini and R. Morandi, Local RBF approximation for
 scattered data fitting with bivarite splines, in "Trends and Applications 
 in Constructive Approximation," (M. G. de Bruin, D. H. Mache, and J. Szabados, Eds.),
 ISNM Vol. 151, Birkhauser, 2005, pp. 91-102. 
 Preprint version is available from  http://www.staff.uni-giessen.de/odavydov/local_rbf.html

Other relevant publications:

 J. Haber, F. Zeilfelder, O. Davydov and H.-P. Seidel, Smooth approximation 
 and rendering of large scattered data sets, in "Proceedings of IEEE 
 Visualization 2001," (Th.Ertl, K.Joy and A.Varshney, Eds.), pp.341-347, 
 571, IEEE Computer Society, 2001. 

 O. Davydov, On the approximation power of local least squares polynomials, 
 in  "Algorithms for Approximation IV," (J.Levesley, I.J.Anderson and 
 J.C.Mason, Eds.), pp.346-353, University of Huddersfield, UK, 2002.

 Ch. Rössl, F. Zeilfelder, G. Nürnberger and H.-P. Seidel, Spline 
 approximation of general volumetric data, ACM Solid Modeling 2004. 

For installation instructions, see the file INSTALL

Some documentation and usage examples are available in examples/*

Send bugs, patches, comments or suggestions on TSFIT to
Oleg Davydov <oleg.davydov@math.uni-giessen.de>

